Titolo: F.E.A.R. 3

Anno: 2011

Descrizione: F.E.A.R. 3 (stylized as F.3.A.R.) is a 2011 first-person shooter survival horror video game developed by Day 1 Studios and published by Warner Bros. Interactive Entertainment for Microsoft Windows, PlayStation 3 and Xbox 360. It is the sequel to F.E.A.R. 2: Project Origin and is the third installment of the F.E.A.R. series. John Carpenter directed the cinematics while Steve Niles wrote the game's scenario. It is also the only F.E.A.R. game to have offline multiplayer and co-op. On November 15, 2021, Microsoft announced that in celebration of 20 years of Xbox, they would be adding over 70 more games to their backwards compatibility program. Included in these games was the entirety of the F.E.A.R. franchise, which are now available to be purchased and played on Microsoft's Xbox One and Xbox Series X/S Consoles.

Genere: First-person shooter

